name: Flareon
flavorText: Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokemon's body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has a Memory Capsule attached, Grass Pokemon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

name: Vaporeon
flavorText: When Vaporeon's fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has a Memory Capsule attached, Fire Pokemon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

name: Octillery
flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Rapid Strike card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. You can't use more than 1 Rapid Strike Search Ability each turn.

name: Jolteon
flavorText: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has a Memory Capsule attached, Water Pokemon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

name: Zekrom
flavorText: When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 60 damage to itself. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Dusknoir
flavorText: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokemon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.
Ability1Text: All Special Energy attached to Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's) provide Colorless Energy and have no other effect.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: Since Dedenne can't generate as much electricity on its own, it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokemon.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has exactly 1 Prize card remaining, this attack does 60 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Alcremie
flavorText: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your turn does not end when you use Cafe Master.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each type of basic Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Ariados
flavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Evolution Pokemon with their Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Houndoom
flavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Single Strike Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Single Strike Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck. If you attached Energy to a Pokemon in this way, put 2 damage counters on that Pokemon.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokemon conceals many different possible evolutions.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Pokemon V, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Oranguru
flavorText: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokemon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch a card from your hand with the top card of your deck.

name: Boltund V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Lightning Energy cards and attach them to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Lightning Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Sylveon V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

name: Sylveon VMAX
Attack1Text: Attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. If you do, heal 120 damage from that Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each different type of Pokemon on your Bench.

name: Mimikyu V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may prevent all damage done to this Mimikyu V by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon until the end of your opponent's next turn.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokemon for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Mimikyu VMAX
Attack1Text: Put 4 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like. If you played Acerola's Premonition from your hand during this turn, place 13 damage counters instead.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Single Strike Urshifu V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Fighting Energy cards and attach them to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Impact Blow.

name: Single Strike Urshifu VMAX
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Rapid Strike Urshifu V
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Rapid Strike Urshifu VMAX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 120 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Umbreon V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Umbreon VMAX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon.

name: Single Strike Urshifu VMAX
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Rapid Strike Urshifu VMAX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 120 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
